.org/detail.php?type=n&nid=2992 |website=South Asia Monitor |accessdate=23 November 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151123092427/http://southasiamonitor.org/detail.php?type=n&nid=2992 |archive-date=23 November 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Now Sindhis Demand Independent Nation In Pakistan|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/world-news-now-sindhi-activists-demand-for-independent-nation-in-pakistan/323750|website=Outlook|access-date=15 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Ethnic group: [[Sindhis|Sindhi]]\n** Proposed state: [[Sindhudesh]] [[File:Flag of Sindhudesh.svg|22px|border]]\n** Political parties: [[Jeay Sindh Qaumi Mahaz]], [[Jeay Sindh Muttahida Mahaz]], [[Sindh United Party]]\n** Student organization: [[Jeay Sindh Students' Federation]]\n\n[[File:Flag of Gilgit Baltistan.svg|22px|border]] [[Gilgit-Baltistan]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Balti people]]\n** Proposed state: [[Balawaristan]] [[File:Flag of Balawaristan.svg|22px|border]]\n** Political party: [[Balawaristan National Front|\nBalawaristan National Front (Hameed group)]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/21-May-2019/raw-network-busted-in-gb?show=preview|title=RAW network busted in GB|date=21 May 2019|work=The Nation|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190521224017/https://nation.com.pk/21-May-2019/raw-network-busted-in-gb?show=preview|archive-date=21 May 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[Gilgit-Baltistan United Movement]]\n\n== Philippines ==\n{{Main|Secession in the Philippines}}\n\n[[Bangsamoro (political entity)|Bangsamoro Region]]\n*Ethnic group: [[Moro people|Moro]]\n** Proposed state: Merger with  {{flag|Malaysia|name=Malaysia}} under the state of {{flag|Sabah|name=Sabah}}\n*** Militant organization: [[Abu Sayyaf]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pike |first1=John |title=Abu Sayyaf Group (ASG) |url=https://fas.org/irp/world/para/asg.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060504010101/https://fas.org/irp/world/para/asg.htm |website=