der]] [[Turkmeneli]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Iraqi Turkmen|Turkmen]]\n** Proposed state: [[Turkmeneli]] [[File:Flag of Iraq Turkmen Front.svg|22px|border]] or unification with [[Turkey]]\n** Political party: [[Iraqi Turkmen Front]] (member of the [[Unrepresented Nations and Peoples Organization]])\n\n[[Sinjar Mountain|Sinjar]] {{citation needed|date=July 2017}}\n* Ethnoreligious group: [[Yazidi]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: [[Sinjar]] with [[Sinjar Mountain]] region in {{flag|Iraq}} or unification with {{flag|Kurdistan}}\n** Political organisation: [[Yazidi Movement for Reform and Progress]], [[Yazidis]] Community\n\n== Japan ==\n{{Main|Secession in Japan}}\n\n[[File:Flag of Hokkaido Prefecture.svg|22px|border]] [[Hokkaido]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fourwinds10.net/siterun_data/peace_freedom/patriots_and_protesters/news.php?q=1239483589 |title=FULFORD: An Independent Movement Has Started in Japan's Northern Island of Hokkaido >> Four Winds 10 \u2013 Truth Winds |first=Chris |last=Donahue |website=fourwinds10.net |access-date=12 May 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502031842/http://www.fourwinds10.net/siterun_data/peace_freedom/patriots_and_protesters/news.php?q=1239483589 |archive-date=2 May 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://asiangazette.blogspot.com/2010/02/ainu-claim-independence-to-prime.html |title=Asian Gazette Blog \u270d Jo\u00ebl Legendre-Koizumi: Ainu claim independence to Prime Minister Hatoyama |first=Joel |last=Legendre |date=7 February 2010 |access-date=12 May 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502005715/http://asiangazette.blogspot.com/2010/02/ainu-claim-independence-to-prime.html |archive-date=2 May 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Ethnic group: [[Ainu people|Ainu]]\n** Proposed state: [[Republic of Ainu]]\n** Advocacy group: {{ill|Ainu Liberation Alliance|lt=Ainu Liberation Alliance|ja|\u30a2\u30a4\u30cc\u89e3\u653e\u540c\u76df}}\n** Political parties: [[Ainu Party]] (\u30a2\u30a4\u30cc\u6c